      <h2>40°</h2>

      <div class="content">

      <p>Sky clear as crystal<br>
	Stretching unhindered between the poles<br>
	Of heaven, from the hills<br>
	To the brilliant sea
      </p>

      <p>A school of pelicans twist across blue unblemished<br>
	By our concerns<br>
	Turning and fading from view,<br>
	And returning, clustered beads of white
      </p>

      <p>Between the relics of my eyes<br>
	As the sirens begin their piercing sound<br>
	The beads of sweat grow along my brow
      </p>

      <p>And the pelicans leave, stage right<br>
	And the next faintly waved blow of breeze<br>
	Brings a cluster of little grass seeds
      </p>

      <p>Dancing daintily on the wind<br>
	In their domain, this vast blazing land<br>
	It is theirs, and<br>
	I can only sit in the shade.
      </p>

      <p>They rise forcefully in columns<br>
	The engines run past<br>
	And float down in the silence,<br>
	Gracefully avoiding towels, trees, and warm steel
      </p>

      <p>This land cannot be brought to heel<br>
	But by softness —
      </p>

      <p>My washing's dry;<br>
	A tiny seed plants itself<br>
	Against my chest.
      </p>

      </div>
      
